-- Bahrain's BKK Says Plans $500 Million Bond Issue After Market 'Stabilizes'
-- Inal Ersan
-- 2010-07-05T05:11:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/bahrain-s-bkk-says-plans-500-million-bond-issue-after-market-stabilizes-.html

          
          
             BBK, the Bahrain-based retail lender
formerly known as Bank of Bahrain & Kuwait, will consider
selling $500 million after the market “stabilizes.”  
 The bank was responding to a report in Al Wasat newspaper
that the company may issue bonds in a few days.  
